en.expected_outputs:
• Achieve a number of enterprises and research institutes participating in transnational research projects;
•  The at-sea testing of the Magallanes and Sabella devices both constitute pilot actions that will immediately impact the development of the partners’ technologies, and will inform the development of the reliability/monitoring tool that will be produced;
•  The reliability/monitoring tool is one of the most important planned outputs and it is expected to have the strongest long-term impact on the development of the tidal energy sector in the Atlantic Area. This is a new-to-the-market product that will provide Tidal Energy Converter (TEC) developers with certainty regarding blade/structure reliability, and will thereby accelerate Blue Growth;
•  The project’s communication/dissemination plan will make use of the established contact network of the partnership, as well as regular tidal sector events that are well-attended by the project’s target audience (i.e., TEC developers, supply chain organisations, research institutes, public authorities etc.) to maximise the impact of the project outputs.

en.expected_results:
• Transfer of technology to energetic companies and services to support local entrepreneurship and SMEs related to geothermal energy: 4 technology transfer experiences to boost innovation in the geothermal energy;
• A resource centre for promoting geothermal energy for districts and buildings (both for electricity and heating/cooling) with an online Advisory Service will be set up;
• At the end of the project a public demonstration project will be implemented in each territory and the integration of measures in favour geothermal energy in the local policy framework will be achieved.

• Development of Standard Analytical Methods to implement a better seafood control for decreasing mislabeling. Consumers provided with trustworthy information through reliable labels;
• Creation of a self-sustained Network of Expertise: a referent body for academia, industry and public authorities at international level, with joint problem-solving capacity to meet future challenges on this field.
• Development and pilot implementation of a Virtual Reference Center for Seafood Authentication: improved and harmonized performance on Seafood Traceability and Labeling control by competent authorities; 
• Recommendations for improved seafood labels arisen from the close collaboration between consumers and industry at transnational level. Involvement of EU Consumers associations, CoR and relevant stakeholder associations to promote better labels. Strategy for consumers’ information;

